Package Attributes

Class ConceptAttribute

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractObjects.ItemWithId
      • Attributes.Attribute
        • Attributes.ConceptAttribute
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ConceptAttribute
extends Attribute
implements java.io.Serializable
    This attribute type models binary relations between concepts. The relations may be from Concept types to Concept types (e.g. friends : Person to Person), Various properties of relations are supported (reflexivity, symmetry, transitivity), and a mapping to inverse relations.
    See Also:

      • stream

        public java.util.stream.Stream<DataObject> stream​(Concept concept,
                                                  Scope scope,
                                                  Operators operator,
                                                  DataObject otherValue,
                                                  java.lang.Object otherConstraints,
                                                  Context context)
        generates a stream of values.
        Example:
        Concept Smith, attribute friends
        friends.stream(Smith,true) would generate a stream of Smith's friends.
        Only transitivity is handled in this method. Symmetry and Reflexivity must be handled somewhere else.
        Specified by:
        stream in class Attribute
        Parameters:
        concept - the concept for which the stream is to be generated.
        scope - the scope of the value to be returned.
        operator - an operator
        otherValue - for comparing: 'this operator otherValue
        otherConstraints - for comparing this.constraints implies otherConstraints
        context - the context
        Returns:
        a stream of attribute values.

      • parseString

        public static ConceptAttribute parseString​(java.lang.String type,
                                           java.lang.String name,
                                           java.lang.String declaration,
                                           java.lang.String namespace,
                                           Context context,
                                           java.lang.StringBuilder errors,
                                           int lineNumber,
                                           DataBlock dataBlock)
        Parses a conceptAttribute declaration: reflexive,symmetric,transitive,functional [domain = domain] [range = range] [inverse = inverse]; All parameters are optional. Notice that attributes with inverse which are either reflexive, symmetric or transitive must have equal domain and range.
        Parameters:
        type - must be 'ConceptAttribute'
        name - the applicationName of the attribute
        declaration - the attribute declaration
        context - the context where the objects live in.
        errors - for appending error messages
        dataBlock - the origin of the definition.
        Returns:
        a new ConceptAttribute or null if an error occurred.
